label: University of Pennsylvania Ms. Codex 681: Book of hours
attribution: Provided by the University of Pennsylvania Libraries
description:
Summary: Fragment of a book of hours, French script, use of Sarum [?]. Misbound: includes Ad laudes (f. 1r-v, f. 7-10); Matins (f. 3r-6v), ending in the middle of the Te Deum; commemoration of St. Anne (f. 2r); commemoration of St. Catherine.
        Language: Latin
        Support: parchment
        Extent: 
        Collation: 
        Layout: Written in 21 long lines; frame-ruled in ink.
        Script: Written in a Gothic script by a single hand.
        Decoration: Wide illuminated border and illuminated 6-line initial (f. 1r); wide decorative border and fully colored 6-line miniature of St. Catherine (f. 2v); initials decorated in gold, red, and blue throughout.
        Binding: Modern red morocco, upper cover detached.
        Origin: Written in France in the second half of the 15th century.
        Cite as:	
        UPenn Ms. Codex 681
        For catalog record, see Permanent Link: 2487467 http://hdl.library.upenn.edu/1017/d/medren/2487467
  For TEI description and digital images, see: http://openn.library.upenn.edu/Data/PennManuscripts/html/mscodex681.html
